    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Path to Irrelevance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David S Wachsman letter about April 15 article on New York Philharmonic says orchestra needs young people in audience (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Passing the Baton: Be Bold, New York [April 15]:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Passing the Baton: Be Bold, New York [April 15]:</p>
        <p>Bravo to Anthony Tommasini for seeking to rouse the New York Philharmonic from its 19th-century, middle European torpor. I am a white-haired subscriber of nearly 30 years and my recent renewals have been based almost entirely on my respect for the musicians and my hope that things will change. I see very few young people in the subscription audience. I hear virtually no buzz about the Philharmonic outside Avery Fisher Hall. Our orchestra is slipping into irrelevance. Mr. Tommasini has pointed the only way into the future.</p>
        <p>David S. Wachsman  Manhattan</p>
        <p>PHILHARMONIC LEADER</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
